My friends and I have officially made this our weekly Sunday brunch spot. Their "secret garden" patio is eclectic and a great place to enjoy your meal. I typically have their omelet which is always cooked to perfection, with up to 6 add ins of your choice. The service at times can be a bit weird, I never know who my actual server is because we have almost every employee come up to our table at some point or another. However, over attentiveness is better than the latter. Definitely a stop worth checking out in the Melrose district.

